<h1>Feedzirra and Rails 3</h1>
<p><a href="https://github.com/pauldix/feedzirra">Feedzirra</a> is probably one of the
best Ruby RSS parsers. But if you&#39;re using it with Rails 3, you may get
an error message like so:</p>
<p><code>no such file to load -- active_support/core_ext/time</code></p>
<p>If that happens, locate your feedzirra.rb file on your machine and
comment out the lines:</p>
<pre><code class="lang-ruby"><span class="comment">#require 'active_support/core_ext/object'</span>
<span class="comment">#require 'active_support/core_ext/time'</span></code></pre>
<p>Add these lines:</p>
<pre><code class="lang-ruby"><span class="keyword">require</span> <span class="string">'active_support/core_ext'</span>
<span class="keyword">require</span> <span class="string">'active_support/time'</span></code></pre>
<p>Are you a <a href="http://gitpilot.com">Git</a> user? Let me help you make project
management with Git simple. Checkout <a href="http://gitpilot.com">Gitpilot</a>.</p>
